data.reasoningText:
Two failures:

1. `DeleteConfirmed_InvalidId_RedirectsToIndexWithError` - The controller calls `db.Students.Find(id)` which returns null, then tries to access properties on it. The exception is `NullReferenceException` because the controller code doesn't handle this - it accesses `student.FirstMidName` etc. before removing. The TempData error is in the catch block but the NullReferenceException happens before the try/catch. Actually looking at the code, it IS inside try/catch. Let me look again...

```csharp
public ActionResult DeleteConfirmed(int id)


{
    try
    {
        Student student = db.Students.Find(id);
        var studentName = $"{student.FirstMidName} {student.LastName}"; // NullReferenceException here
        db.Students.Remove(student);
        ...
```

The NullReferenceException gets thrown when trying to access properties on the null student object. The catch block should catch this Exception and set TempData with the error message, then redirect to Index. But the test is failing, which means either the exception isn't being caught properly or the redirect isn't happening as expected.

Looking at the stack trace more carefully, the exception is propagating all the way to the test instead of being handled. I'm wondering if TempData isn't properly initialized in the test context—when using DefaultHttpContext, TempData might not be set up correctly, which could cause issues when trying to store the error message. The line number mismatch is because TempData isn't initialized in the test context - when the catch block tries to set the error message, it fails since there's no ITempDataDictionaryFactory configured. I can either mock out the TempData provider properly, or adjust the test to expect the exception that occurs when TempData isn't available. For the InstructorsController test, there's a similar issue where `PopulateAssignedCourseData` gets called even when ModelState is invalid.

The problem is that the instructor object passed in has a null `CourseAssignments` collection, so when the method tries to select course IDs from it, it throws a null reference exception. I need to initialize the `CourseAssignments` property on the test instructor before the method runs.

